Therefore, linear monters began an operation to save the nest, and not for the first time in our practice.
Helped by ornithologists from Dnipropetrovsk National University, who have developed a scheme for the transfer of the nest.
They also conducted trainings for employees of district networks.
Famous Dnipropetrovsk ornithologist Alexander Ponomarenko advised power engineers at all stages of the reconstruction of the nests.
To begin with, it was estimated that in the area in the emergency condition there are more than 50 aristine "apartments."
For their reconstruction were welded special metal platforms, resembling a funnel.
The base was splintered with willow branches, and then moved the old nest there.
According to the experts, it is enough to lay the old branches as the basis so that the birds recognize the nest and return to it.
The statists will build their own home.
A month ago, the first nest was reconstructed in the village of Peschanka of Novomoskovsk district.
Next to the electric pole put a new reinforced concrete pole and placed on it a platform with an old, already inhabited nest.
The whole operation cost the power engineers nine thousand hryvnias.
And the other day, the same housewarming took place in the village of Ivanovka, Petrikovsky district, at the estate of grandmother Ani.
Here the platform was fixed in the same place, only lifted over the wires.
Ornithologists are sure that cautious, conservative birds will not even notice in the spring that their "apartment" has undergone major repairs.
Until the end of the year, the same reconstruction awaits four more nests in the Pokrovsky and Tsarichansky districts of the Dnipropetrovsk region.
By the way, while some save rare birds, others ruthlessly kill them.
The other day, the whole area flew around the sad news - in the village of Ust-Kamenka, Apostolovsky district, on the day of the opening of the hunt for the phalans, poachers for entertainment shot a swan family, who lived on a local pond.
