The interest policy of the Central Bank does not affect market rates, affects only the rates of interbank lending.
"For the Central Bank, this is the collapse of all hopes," Clemens Grafe estimated.
The money received at the auctions of the Central Bank, banks are used not for lending to the economy, but to manage their liquidity
As soon as the rate decreases, the exchange rate immediately changes, it means that the funds are trying to go on speculation against the ruble.
