Syria Destroyed Equipment for Chemical Weapons
Syria destroyed all declared chemical weapons production facilities, the Organization for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons.
This first phase of disarmament was completed by Damascus the day before the deadline.
Until November 1, Syria was to destroy production and other auxiliary facilities designed to prepare combat poisonous substances for use.
The destruction of the stockpiles of toxic substances or their chemical components should be completed by mid-2014.
